# Spring Boot Project Generator

## When to activate

Activate this rule whenever the user asks to:
- Create / generate / scaffold a new Spring Boot project
- Use start.spring.io or Spring Initializr from the terminal
- Add dependencies to a new Spring Boot app (web, JPA, security, etc.)

Do NOT activate for questions about an *existing* Spring Boot project.

---

## Script location

```
spring-boot-initializr/scripts/spring-initializr.py
```

Install dependencies once:

```bash
pip install -r spring-boot-initializr/scripts/requirements.txt
```

---

## Quick generation

```bash
python spring-boot-initializr/scripts/spring-initializr.py generate \
  --groupId <group> \
  --artifactId <artifact> \
  --dependencies <dep1,dep2,...>
```

**All other flags are optional** — the script fills in sensible defaults (Gradle, Java 17, latest stable Spring Boot).

---

## Common flags

| Flag | Default | Notes |
|------|---------|-------|
| `--type` | `gradle-project` | also `maven-project`, `gradle-project-kotlin` |
| `--javaVersion` | `17` | check supported values with `--list-versions` |
| `--language` | `java` | also `kotlin`, `groovy` |
| `--bootVersion` | latest stable | omit to always get the latest |
| `--packageName` | derived | strip hyphens/underscores from artifactId |
| `--output-dir` | current dir | write project to a specific path |
| `--force` | — | bypass 1-hour metadata cache |

---

## Dependency quick-reference

| User says | Use ID |
|-----------|--------|
| REST API, MVC | `web` |
| Reactive / WebFlux | `webflux` |
| JPA / Hibernate | `data-jpa` |
| MySQL | `mysql` |
| PostgreSQL | `postgresql` |
| H2 in-memory DB | `h2` |
| Redis / cache | `data-redis` |
| MongoDB | `data-mongodb` |
| Security / login | `security` |
| OAuth2 client | `oauth2-client` |
| JWT / resource server | `oauth2-resource-server` |
| Kafka | `kafka` |
| RabbitMQ | `amqp` |
| Batch processing | `batch` |
| Actuator / monitoring | `actuator` |
| Lombok | `lombok` |
| DevTools (hot reload) | `devtools` |
| Testcontainers | `testcontainers` |
| Thymeleaf | `thymeleaf` |
| GraphQL | `graphql` |
| WebSocket | `websocket` |

> ⚠️ Spring Cloud deps (`cloud-config-client`, `cloud-eureka`, `cloud-gateway`) require a
> compatible Spring Cloud BOM — check https://spring.io/projects/spring-cloud#overview.

---

## packageName rule

Java package names must be lowercase, no hyphens, no underscores.
The script auto-derives it, but always double-check:

- `user-service`  → `com.example.userservice`
- `order_manager` → `com.example.ordermanager`

Override: `--packageName com.example.mypackage`

---

## Exploration commands

```bash
# What Boot versions are available?
python spring-boot-initializr/scripts/spring-initializr.py --list-versions

# What dependencies exist?
python spring-boot-initializr/scripts/spring-initializr.py --list-deps
python spring-boot-initializr/scripts/spring-initializr.py --list-deps --category web

# Find a dependency by keyword
python spring-boot-initializr/scripts/spring-initializr.py --search-deps redis

# Validate before generating
python spring-boot-initializr/scripts/spring-initializr.py --validate-deps web,data-jpa,mysql
```

---

## Post-generation: DB config snippet

If the project includes `data-jpa` + `mysql` or `postgresql`, remind the user to edit
`src/main/resources/application.properties`:

```properties
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/{artifactId}
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=yourpassword
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
```

---

## Example

User: *"Create a Spring Boot project, group com.acme, artifact order-service, add web, JPA, PostgreSQL, Lombok"*

```bash
python spring-boot-initializr/scripts/spring-initializr.py generate \
  --groupId com.acme \
  --artifactId order-service \
  --packageName com.acme.orderservice \
  --dependencies web,data-jpa,postgresql,lombok
```
